- Waste and Recycling Guidelines
Iowa State University generates a wide variety of waste materials. These materials range from common paper trash and glass to hazardous items such as chemicals, appliances, computers, and radioactive materials. The Waste and Recycling Guide provides information to Iowa State University personnel regarding the management of waste items, including identification, disposal, recycling, and waste minimization. - What Not to Burn Poster
Examples of items that should not be incinerated according to the university incinerator procedures. - What Not to Flush Poster
Examples of items that shouldn't be flushed down drains. - Workplace Hazard Assessment for Personnel with Animal Contact
Personnel with animal contact should use this form to assist them in determining and mitigating the hazards found in their workplace. - X-ray Inspection Criteria
These criteria are used for areas posted and approved for X-ray or radiation-producing device use. - X-Ray or Radiation-Producing Device Authorization Application
- X-ray Safety Manual
